home, books were my escape.

00:10:03.420 --> 00:10:06.990
They were proof that there
was a world -- thank you.

00:10:06.990 --> 00:10:08.450
I'm short, sorry.

00:10:08.450 --> 00:10:12.410
There was proof that there was
a world out there that was big

00:10:12.410 --> 00:10:16.280
and broad and it was full of
hope and people doing things

00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:18.980
that didn't happen
where I came from.

00:10:18.980 --> 00:10:20.580
So books were my escape.

00:10:20.580 --> 00:10:24.470
And because of them and the
love of literature that I grew

00:10:24.470 --> 00:10:27.780
from my local library, because
we certainly didn't have money

00:10:27.780 --> 00:10:32.120
to go to Barnes &amp; Noble, I
became the person I am today

00:10:32.120 --> 00:10:35.510
which loves books and loves
literature and is so proud

00:10:35.510 --> 00:10:38.170
and honored to be a part of
the National Book Festival

00:10:38.170 --> 00:10:39.500
and the Library of Congress.

00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:41.010
It truly is one of
the highlights

00:10:41.010 --> 00:10:44.490
of the great things I get to
do for kids all year long.

00:10:44.490 --> 00:10:46.120
Being a judge for the Book

00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:50.690
That Shaped Me contest is
a nerd's greatest goal.

00:10:50.690 --> 00:10:52.380
