00:15:33.740 --> 00:15:35.800
second place grand prize winner

00:15:35.800 --> 00:15:39.540
and the Virginia State
winner Miss Aria Patnaik.

00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:42.270
She wrote about "One
for the Murphys".

00:15:42.270 --> 00:15:44.920
And I tell you, after
reading her essay,

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:47.860
it made me want to
read this book.

00:15:47.860 --> 00:15:51.580
This young lady managed to tell
quite the story with her words

00:15:51.580 --> 00:15:55.120
and we'll be happy to hear that
from her in just a few moments.

00:16:02.020 --> 00:16:04.770
&gt;&gt; Aria Patnaik: "One for the
Murphys" is a book about family,

00:16:04.770 --> 00:16:07.580
strength, heroes,
and most of all,

00:16:07.580 --> 00:16:09.700
what it feels like to be loved.

00:16:09.700 --> 00:16:13.840
Carley Connors has a
mother who throws parties,

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:15.840
drinks too much alcohol,
and can't bear to say

00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:18.180
"I love you" to her
own daughter.

00:16:18.180 --> 00:16:21.990
When Carley's abusive stepdad
hurts her and her mother,

00:16:21.990 --> 00:16:25.110
Carley is forced into foster
care with the Murphy's,

00:16:25.110 --> 00:16:28.140
an affectionate family with a
mother who gives Carley a voice

00:16:28.140 --> 00:16:31.240
and makes her realize
what she's been missing.

00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:34.750
This book has left an impact
on me for multiple reasons.

00:16:34.750 --> 00:16:38.300
First, it taught me that there
is no need to try to be tough

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:42.120
because a little
sensitivity is only natural.

00:16:42.120 --> 00:16:44.970
Second, it made me realize
the true value of family

00:16:44.970 --> 00:16:46.270
and the love they provide.

00:16:46.270 --> 00:16:48.120
And lastly, I learned
what it feels

00:16:48.120 --> 00:16:52.010
like to be a castaway
or apart from normal.

00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:54.500
This beautiful story provides
a behind the scenes look

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:57.630
at a strong girl with
a sensitive heart.

00:16:57.630 --> 00:16:59.390
Growing up with two
older brothers,

00:16:59.390 --> 00:17:01.530
people expect me to be tough.

00:17:01.530 --> 00:17:04.250
They expect tears to
be a foreign language.

00:17:04.250 --> 00:17:06.380
Carley has taught me that
being tough is different

00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:07.820
than being strong.

00:17:07.820 --> 00:17:11.440
The exact definition of tough
is not easily broken or cut,

00:17:11.440 --> 00:17:15.860
while the definition of strong
is accompanied by great power.

00:17:15.860 --> 00:17:18.740
This means physically
but also mentally.

00:17:18.740 --> 00:17:21.350
You go forth and
face your obstacles.

00:17:21.350 --> 00:17:25.020
As Julie Murphy says, "It's
easier to lock yourself away.

00:17:25.020 --> 00:17:28.480
It takes strength to face
things that scare you."

00:17:28.480 --> 00:17:31.750
I no longer feel like if
I have feelings, I'm weak.

00:17:31.750 --> 00:17:34.430
I finally feel free and human.

00:17:34.430 --> 00:17:38.490
I've discovered my emotions
and a whole new side of myself.

00:17:38.490 --> 00:17:40.710
"One for the Murphys"
left me feeling lucky,

00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:42.850
blessed, and thankful.

00:17:42.850 --> 00:17:44.740
Oftentimes, I find
myself complaining

00:17:44.740 --> 00:17:47.630
about my annoying brothers
or whining to my parents

00:17:47.630 --> 00:17:49.520
because something isn't fair.

00:17:49.520 --> 00:17:52.010
But after reading this book, I
realized that it's all just part

00:17:52.010 --> 00:17:54.500
of the definition of family.

00:17:54.500 --> 00:17:57.150
One line from the
book caught my eye.

00:17:57.150 --> 00:18:00.350
"The way she reached in,
pulled me out, dusted me off,

00:18:00.350 --> 00:18:03.660
and said that I only needed
to be the great person I am."

00:18:03.660 --> 00:18:06.010
I realized that that's
exactly what family does.

00:18:06.010 --> 00:18:08.370
They take you under their
wing when you're broken,

00:18:08.370 --> 00:18:11.040
heal your wound,
and tell you to fly.

00:18:11.040 --> 00:18:13.160
So many people don't
get tucked in at night,

00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:21.320
so many people don't get to
eat dinner with their family,

00:18:21.320 --> 00:18:24.940
and so many people don't get to
play catch with their brothers.

00:18:24.940 --> 00:18:27.270
A family is something you
can lean on in times of worry

00:18:27.270 --> 00:18:30.220
or sadness, and yet so many
people don't have that.

00:18:30.220 --> 00:18:32.420
Carley really highlighted
all the perks of a family

00:18:32.420 --> 00:18:36.310
that I see every day
yet take for granted.

00:18:36.310 --> 00:18:38.740
All my life, I've
never been the new kid.

00:18:38.740 --> 00:18:40.820
I've never felt different
or an outcast.

00:18:40.820 --> 00:18:42.730
My whole life is familiar.

00:18:42.730 --> 00:18:45.490
I've never moved schools
or houses and that's why

00:18:45.490 --> 00:18:47.790
when my parents told me
that for seventh grade,

00:18:47.790 --> 00:18:50.720
I'm going to a private school
where I don't know anybody

00:18:50.720 --> 00:18:52.510
and where there are
probably some mean girls,

00:18:52.510 --> 00:18:55.590
I have to admit I was scared.

00:18:55.590 --> 00:18:56.890
This wonderful look

00:18:56.890 --> 00:18:58.730
into Carley's thoughts
have shown me what it feels

00:18:58.730 --> 00:19:01.460
like to stand apart
from everyone else.

00:19:01.460 --> 00:19:04.560
An example from the book is
when Carley says, "I was right

00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:06.220
about being a foster kid.

00:19:06.220 --> 00:19:07.870
It is humiliating."

00:19:07.870 --> 00:19:11.080
When people put labels on
you, it's hard to escape them.

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:12.890
It's hard to know that you're
not like everyone else.

00:19:12.890 --> 00:19:15.900
And it takes time to
realize that that's okay.

00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:19.380
Carley has taught me that change
is okay and it happens fast,

00:19:19.380 --> 00:19:22.790
and though it may be difficult,
you just have to adjust.

00:19:22.790 --> 00:19:25.110
Carley is always strong and
stays confident no matter

00:19:25.110 --> 00:19:29.580
where she is, and I think
everyone can learn from that.

00:19:29.580 --> 00:19:32.190
I've read this book three
times, each at different stages

00:19:32.190 --> 00:19:36.270
of my life and each time
this book has helped me

00:19:36.270 --> 00:19:38.070
for different reasons.

00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:40.890
It has taught me valuable
lessons that help me every day.

00:19:40.890 --> 00:19:42.650
Just like Julie Murphy
stuck with Carley,

00:19:42.650 --> 00:19:44.220
"One for the Murphys"
stuck with me

00:19:44.220 --> 00:19:45.580
and will always stick with me.

00:19:45.580 --> 00:19:48.810
When I finished "One for the
Murphys," new thoughts sprung

00:19:48.810 --> 00:19:50.410
into my head that I'd
never thought of before.

00:19:50.410 --> 00:19:53.320
I thought about why some
parents can handle kids

00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:54.620
and some parents can't.

00:19:54.620 --> 00:19:57.130
I thought about what I
would do if I had to choose

00:19:57.130 --> 00:19:59.290
between a loving and
supportive family

00:19:59.290 --> 00:20:02.280
and a neglectful but fun mom.

00:20:02.280 --> 00:20:05.530
"One for the Murphys" is about
what strong really means,

00:20:05.530 --> 00:20:07.690
always staying confident
and the importance

00:20:07.690 --> 00:20:10.510
and many forms of family.

00:20:10.510 --> 00:20:18.080
